Mission Finder is a closed-source project. This repository publishes only the
addon's documentation and screenshots. The source code is intentionally not made
public.


Why this project is closed source
---------------------------------
Mission Finder detects which guild missions are currently active, and which of
their targets you have completed, by reading the Guild Wars 2 client's memory,
which relies on reverse engineering of the game client. Publishing the source
would also publish those reverse-engineering details, so the code is kept
private.

Mission Finder only reads the game's memory; it never writes to or modifies the
game's memory or code. A couple of actions that you trigger yourself — clicking a
mission to copy its waypoint to the clipboard or post it to chat — are carried
out by sending ordinary keyboard input, to reproduce something you could already
do by hand. Mission Finder does not alter game state directly, inject code into
the game, bot, or automate gameplay.


Permitted use
-------------
You may download and use the Mission Finder addon free of charge, including while
streaming, recording, or making videos or other content — on monetised channels
as well as personal ones. Streamers and content creators are warmly welcome to
feature and showcase Mission Finder. You may also quote or reuse this
repository's documentation and screenshots when describing, reviewing, or
showcasing Mission Finder, with attribution.

This permission does not let you sell Mission Finder, charge others for access to
it, or bundle it into a paid product or service — see Restrictions below.


Restrictions
------------
Except as expressly permitted above, you may not copy, modify, redistribute,
sell, decompile, disassemble, or otherwise reverse engineer the Mission Finder
software or attempt to recover its source code, without prior written permission
from the author.


ArenaNet developer access
-------------------------
The author welcomes scrutiny from the people who make Guild Wars 2. Verified
ArenaNet employees may request read-only access to the complete source code in
order to review Mission Finder's behaviour and confirm its compliance with the
Guild Wars 2 User Agreement and rules of conduct. To request access, contact the
author by opening an issue on this repository, via the contact form at
https://pie.rocks.cc/, or by having a GM contact PieOrCake.7635 in-game.
Such access is granted for review purposes only and conveys no license to use,
copy, modify, or redistribute the source code.


